The refugees have been living around Greenmarket Square since October, saying they feel unsafe living among South African communities. CAPE TOWN - Hotel managers near the Central Methodist Church - where refugees have been staying for the past four months - say their presence has become a safety risk for their guests. READ: Motsoaledi on Cape refugees: Government's hands are tied The General Manager at 40 on Burg Hotel says their presence has become a safety risk for her guests. She says some groups have settled right outside the hotel's entrance and she's had to escort guests in and out of the building as a result. READ: Cape Town refugees feel 'unsafe' Garth Kent from the Mandela Rhodes Place Hotel and Spa said, "business has really dropped terribly." He related some business owners have been threatened and hygiene has become an issue in the area.